goals.question: What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of US_Gross vs Worldwide_Gross
goals.rationale: This will help us understand the relationship between the US and worldwide gross revenue of the movies and identify any outliers.

goals.question: What is the distribution of Production_Budget?

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Release_Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Release_Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x='US_Gross', y='Worldwide_Gross', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Production_Budget'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Production_Budget'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Production_Budget', kde=True)
    plt.xlabel('Production Budget')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Production_Budget?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
